# 🔵 Part 2（1.5分钟）

## 🎤 Describe a book you like

---

## 🎯 8.0 Answer

> I’d like to talk about a book that I really enjoyed reading, which is called *Atomic Habits*.
> I read this book about a year ago when I was trying to improve my daily habits.
>
> The book mainly talks about how small changes in our daily routines can lead to significant improvements over time.
> What I found particularly interesting is that it gives very practical advice, such as how to build good habits step by step.
>
> For example, it suggests starting with very small goals, like reading just one page a day, which makes it much easier to stay consistent.
>
> Overall, I found this book extremely helpful and inspiring, because it completely changed the way I think about self-improvement.

---

### 🇨🇳 翻译

我想谈一本我非常喜欢的书，叫《原子习惯》。
我是在大约一年前，当我想改善自己日常习惯的时候读的这本书。

这本书主要讲的是，日常生活中的小改变如何随着时间带来巨大的提升。
我觉得特别有意思的是，它提供了很多非常实用的建议，比如如何一步一步建立好习惯。

例如，它建议从非常小的目标开始，比如每天只读一页书，这样更容易坚持。

总的来说，我觉得这本书非常有帮助，也很有启发性，因为它彻底改变了我对自我提升的看法。

---

